WARNING! From March 23, 2024, free evacuation to territorial communities of Rivne Oblast will begin! Mandatory evacuation of civilian residents will be redirected from Zhytomyr to Rivne Oblast from March 23.
Evacuation to the Rivne region will be carried out by a special train, once every 8 days (23.03; 31.03; 08.04; 16.04; 24.04).

In order to save their lives, leave for a safe region and get free accommodation, Kramators need:

• leave an application by calling 097-804-20-89;
• get to the gathering place in the community (you will be informed by phone - where exactly), from where there will be a free ride to the evacuation train in the city of Pokrovsk.

For the evacuation of seriously ill and disabled persons, please call the following numbers: 0800332614, 0997104872, 0993115314, 0961086048.

Social guarantees:
• free accommodation in communally owned establishments (defined as places of compact accommodation) of the Rivne region;
• monthly payment of accommodation allowance to internally displaced persons;
• one-time payment to the civilian population that is being evacuated;
• humanitarian help;
• psychological assistance;
• medical assistance, etc.

Evacuation is difficult, but necessary! Evacuation saves lives!🇺🇦TG|FB|INST|Site

